

** Basic Docker Commands**

** sudo docker build -t first-docker-app .                                           ==> This command will create docker container.
** sudo docker container run --name=first-docker-cont -d -p 8500:80 first-docker-app ==> This command will run docker container.
** sudo docker tag oldfilename newfilename                                           ==> This command will create copy of image with new name.
** sudo docker image push imagename.                                                 ==> This command will push image to the repo.
** sudo docker login                                                                 ==> By this command we can login.
** sudo docker logout                                                                ==> By this command we can logout. 
** sudo docker image pull imagename                                                  ==> This command will pull image from the repo.

